rs, sprinkle with reserved grated cheese and insert Varoma tray in Varoma dish."},{"content":"Place onions, carrots, 30 g extra virgin olive oil, tomatoes, 1-2 basil leaves, water, vegetable stock paste and ½ tsp salt in mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Insert simmering basket and add mixed vegetables to it. Set Varoma in position and cook <b>30 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma. With aid of baking paper lining, roll up the spinach omelette, keeping it wrapped in the baking paper. Meanwhile remove simmering basket using spatula, transfer cooked vegetables to a shallow serving dish, season with salt to taste and stir. Unwrap the spinach omelette and cut in slices (approx. 2 cm). Transfer slices to serving dish with vegetables and keep warm. Transfer tomato soup to a serving bowl, add reserved steamed garlic bread to the soup, drizzle with some extra virgin olive oil and garnish with roughly torn basil leaves. Serve the soup hot as a starter and the rolled omelette warm as a main dish, with the ratatouille vegetables on the side."}],"hintsAndTricks":["'Pappa al pomodoro', or bread and tomato soup, is classic comfort food in many Italian homes. While the soup is bubbling away, steam the next soothing course: a spinach and cheese rolled omelette presented in beautiful green spirals, served with hearty Mediterranean vegetables on the side.","For a smooth soup, after removing Varoma and simmering basket in <b>step 6,<b> blend <b><strong>1 min\/speed 5-10,<\/strong><b> <strong>increasing speed gradually.<\/strong> Add the steamed garlic bread and serve as described in <b>step 6.<b>","Replace spinach in the rolled omelette with vegetables of your choice (e.g. cabbage, courgette)."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","1h 5m","4 portions"]}